<item>
            <title>[LU-15911] Make enable_filename_encryption tunable only available with embedded llcrypt</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15911</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;enable_filename_encryption&lt;/tt&gt; tunable was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15858&quot; title=&quot;Enable filename encryption separately from data encryption&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15858&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-15858&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. But this only makes sense when Lustre client is built against the embedded llcrypt. When built against in-kernel fscrypt, this tunable is silently ignored, as fscrypt always carries out file name encryption.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
